# KPI Time Horizons: When to Measure What

Understanding which metrics to track at different time intervals, why timing matters, and how to build an effective measurement rhythm.

## The Core Principle

**Not all KPIs should be measured at the same frequency.**

- Some metrics are meaningless daily (client retention)
- Some metrics are critical daily (cash balance)
- Some metrics need monthly review (financial performance)
- Some metrics only matter quarterly (strategic progress)

**Measuring at wrong intervals creates:**
- Analysis paralysis (too frequent)
- Missed problems (too infrequent)
- Wasted effort (wrong metrics)
- False alarms (noise vs. signal)

---

## The Measurement Hierarchy
```
Strategic (Annual/Quarterly)
    ↓
Tactical (Monthly)
    ↓
Operational (Weekly)
    ↓
Pulse (Daily)
```

**Each level serves different purpose.**

---

## Daily Metrics (Pulse Checks)

### Purpose
- Operational health
- Early warning signals
- Maintain momentum
- Identify immediate issues

### Characteristics
- Quick to check (5-10 minutes)
- Actionable same-day
- High variability expected
- Focus on absolutes, not trends

---

### What to Track Daily

**Cash Position:**
- Bank balance
- Accounts receivable aging
- Payables due this week

**Why daily:**
- Cash crisis can happen fast
- Need immediate visibility
- Enables proactive management

**How to track:**
- Bank app check
- Quick spreadsheet glance
- Automated alert if below threshold

**What to do:**
- No action unless threshold crossed
- Just awareness
- Weekly review of trends

---

**Pipeline Activity (Sales Teams Only):**
- New opportunities added
- Activities logged (calls, meetings)
- Deals moved forward

**Why daily:**
- Sales momentum requires consistency
- Daily activity drives weekly results
- Accountability tool

**How to track:**
- CRM dashboard
- Quick team standup
- Activity scoreboard

**What to do:**
- Celebrate wins
- Identify blockers
- Adjust tomorrow's priorities

---

**Team Capacity (Delivery Leaders Only):**
- Who's available today
- Who's overloaded
- Urgent client issues

**Why daily:**
- Resource allocation dynamic
- Client emergencies happen
- Prevent burnout

**How to track:**
- Project management tool
- Team standup
- Slack status

**What to do:**
- Reallocate if needed
- Address urgent issues
- Plan next 24-48 hours

---

### Daily Tracking Best Practices

**Do:**
- Keep it simple (5-minute check)
- Focus on operations, not strategy
- Use dashboards/automation
- Check same time each day

**Don't:**
- Overanalyze daily variance
- React to noise
- Track too many metrics
- Skip days (consistency matters)

---

## Weekly Metrics (Operational Rhythm)

### Purpose
- Operational performance
- Short-term trends
- Course correction
- Team alignment

### Characteristics
- 15-30 minute review
- Enough data for patterns
- Actionable within week
- Balance detail and overview

---

### What to Track Weekly

**Revenue Pipeline:**
- MQLs generated
- SQLs qualified
- Deals in each stage
- Forecasted close this month
- Win/loss for week

**Why weekly:**
- Enough volume for patterns
- Time to course-correct
- Maintains sales momentum
- Monthly revenue preview

**How to track:**
- CRM reports
- Monday sales meeting
- Dashboard review

**What to do:**
- Adjust outreach if MQLs low
- Focus on stalled deals
- Celebrate wins
- Identify coaching needs

---

**Project Delivery:**
- Projects on track vs. at-risk
- Utilization by team/person
- Client satisfaction indicators
- Upcoming deliverables

**Why weekly:**
- Catch issues early
- Resource reallocation possible
- Client communication proactive
- Prevent crisis mode

**How to track:**
- Project management dashboard
- Delivery team meeting
- Client health scores

**What to do:**
- Reallocate resources
- Client communication
- Escalate risks
- Plan next week capacity

---

**Financial Snapshot:**
- Week's invoicing
- Collections this week
- Major expenses
- Cash flow preview

**Why weekly:**
- Enough data to be meaningful
- Early cash warnings
- Invoice timing matters
- Expense visibility

**How to track:**
- Accounting system
- Quick spreadsheet update
- CFO/bookkeeper report

**What to do:**
- Send past-due reminders
- Approve/defer expenses
- Adjust cash forecast
- Plan collections calls

---

**Team Health Pulse:**
- Workload check-ins
- Overtime hours
- Sick days / PTO
- Mood/morale signals

**Why weekly:**
- Burnout prevention
- Capacity planning
- Culture monitoring
- Early intervention

**How to track:**
- Team meetings
- 1-on-1 conversations
- Time tracking data
- Informal observation

**What to do:**
- Address overwork
- Redistribute load
- Give recognition
- Surface concerns

---

### Weekly Tracking Best Practices

**Meeting structure:**
- Same day/time each week
- 30-60 minutes maximum
- Dashboard-driven discussion
- Action items assigned

**Do:**
- Focus on trends, not single points
- Identify early warnings
- Make tactical adjustments
- Keep team accountable

**Don't:**
- Cancel or reschedule
- Let meetings run long
- Discuss strategy (save for monthly)
- Track without action

---

## Monthly Metrics (Tactical Management)

### Purpose
- Performance evaluation
- Trend analysis
- Strategic adjustments
- Accountability

### Characteristics
- 1-2 hour deep dive
- Comprehensive review
- Actionable next month
- Formal documentation

---

### What to Track Monthly

**Financial Performance (Complete):**
- AGI and AGI%
- Revenue by service line
- All cost categories
- EBITDA margin
- Cash position and runway
- AGI per FTE

**Why monthly:**
- Standard accounting cycle
- Enough data for analysis
- Trend visibility
- Meaningful variances

**How to track:**
- Full P&L review
- Dashboard with trends
- Variance analysis
- Year-over-year comparison

**What to do:**
- Celebrate wins
- Address variances
- Adjust budget/forecast
- Strategic decisions

---

**Forecasting & Pipeline:**
- Total forecast (current + pipeline)
- Net MRR movement
- Churn analysis
- Pipeline quality assessment
- Forecast accuracy check

**Why monthly:**
- Sufficient data for trends
- Time for course correction
- Planning cycle alignment
- Variance learning

**How to track:**
- Forecast spreadsheet/tool
- CRM reports
- Variance calculations
- Trend charts

**What to do:**
- Update next quarter forecast
- Adjust hiring plans
- Sales strategy tweaks
- Pipeline health initiatives

---

**Client Retention & Health:**
- Retention rate (monthly + rolling)
- Churn analysis (who and why)
- NPS survey results
- Account health scores
- Upsell/expansion wins

**Why monthly:**
- Meaningful sample size
- Pattern identification
- Proactive intervention time
- Relationship tracking

**How to track:**
- Client database
- Survey results
- Account manager reports
- Dashboard

**What to do:**
- At-risk account outreach
- Celebration of wins
- Process improvements
- Expansion campaigns

---

**Sales & Marketing Performance:**
- Lead generation (MQLs/SQLs)
- Conversion rates (all stages)
- Win rate and loss analysis
- CAC calculation
- Channel performance
- Sales cycle length

**Why monthly:**
- Sufficient conversion data
- Channel ROI visible
